# Development / CI tooling — SOURCE for pip-compile (P13). Not needed at runtime.
#
# Compile (Python 3.11, hashed, cross-platform):
#   uv pip compile --generate-hashes --universal --python-version 3.11 \
#       requirements-dev.in -o requirements-dev.txt
#
# CI installs the compiled requirements-dev.txt with `pip install --require-hashes`.
# NOTE: gitleaks is a compiled Go binary (a GitHub release asset, NOT a PyPI package)
# and is installed separately — see https://github.com/gitleaks/gitleaks#installing
# and .pre-commit-config.yaml. It is intentionally absent from these requirements.

-r requirements.in

